DIGITS.doc: DIGITS(X) returns number of significant binary digits in the model of X. [F90]

EPSILON.doc: EPSILON(X) returns smallest positive number that added to 1 gives result > 1. [F90]

HUGE.doc: HUGE(X) returns largest number representable in the model of X. [F90]

MAXEXPONENT.doc: MAXEXPONENT(X) returns maximum exponent in the floating-point model of X. [F90]

MINEXPONENT.doc: MINEXPONENT(X) returns minimum exponent in the floating-point model of X. [F90]

PRECISION.doc: PRECISION(X) returns decimal precision of real or complex kind of X. [F90]

RADIX.doc: RADIX(X) returns base of the numeric model for X (typically 2 for binary). [F90]

RANGE.doc: RANGE(X) returns decimal exponent range in the model of X. [F90]

TINY.doc: TINY(X) returns smallest positive number in the floating-point model of X. [F90]
